### While Loop

The `while` loop repeatedly executes a block of code as long as a given condition remains true.

---

### Basic Syntax

```cpp
while (condition) {
  // Code to repeat
}
```

---

### Example

```cpp
int i = 0;
while (i < 5) {
  cout << i << " ";
  i++;
}
// Output: 0 1 2 3 4
```

---

### Infinite Loop

```cpp
while (true) {
  // Runs forever (until break)
}
```

---

### Sentinel-Controlled Loop

```cpp
int number;
int sum = 0;

cout << "Enter numbers (negative to stop): ";
cin >> number;

while (number >= 0) {
  sum += number;
  cin >> number;
}
```

---

### Common Patterns

| Pattern | Code |
|---------|------|
| Counter | `while (count < n) { ... count++; }` |
| Sentinel | `while ((c = getchar()) != EOF) { }` |
| Flag | `while (!done) { ... if (cond) done = true; }` |

---

> **Key Point:** Ensure the loop variable changes within the body to avoid infinite loops. The condition is checked before each iteration.

codeExample:
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
  int count = 1;
  while (count <= 5) {
    cout << "Count: " << count << endl;
    count++;
  }
  return 0;
}
